Kidneys are symmetric without concerning lesions or hydronephrosis. Small bowel shows normal caliber without obstruction. A retrocecal fluid-filled appendix measuring 6-7 mm with mild wall hyperemia and thickening. The pelvic organs are unremarkable, and there is a 2.8 cm likely ovarian cyst on the left. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities. No osseous lesions or fractures.
